ASU 2016-18 – Statement of Cash Flows (Topic 230): Restricted Cash
 
During the first quarter of 2018, the Company adopted the accounting guidance issued in 2016 that requires companies
to show the changes in the total of cash, cash equivalents, restricted cash and restricted cash equivalents in the
statement of cash flows. The Company’s restricted cash is primarily associated with acquisitions, and the related escrow
payments. As a result of the new guidance, the Company has updated the policy so restricted cash will no longer be
shown as a transfer on the statement of cash flows, and a reconciliation of restricted cash will be added to the statement
of cash flows.
 
